<paragraph id="75817702B6D8DC84B3CF246A7C355235" lastPageNumber="35" pageNumber="34">
This monotypic genus is only known from the Paraguay River drainage. 
<taxonomicName id="2558AACECE0FF816349CC51299B5FE2C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A27DFC6C-22B0-4D3F-83A8-00E2CF1855E1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pyxiloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pyxiloricaria menezesi Isbrücker &amp; Nijssen 1984:164" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="menezesi">Pyxiloricaria menezesi</taxonomicName>
inhabits sandy substrates and is sympatric with representatives of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="B545A48B9760C4AE09DB28F230042D27" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E805457A-B6F3-4756-950E-1AD4B96002BB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudohemiodon" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudohemiodon Bleeker 1862:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudohemiodon</taxonomicName>
. Sexual dimorphism and reproductive ecology are unknown. In the 
<taxonomicName id="F99A1ADB7748D2D321489984C7134EC8" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E805457A-B6F3-4756-950E-1AD4B96002BB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudohemiodon" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudohemiodon Bleeker 1862:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudohemiodon</taxonomicName>
group, 
<taxonomicName id="B9056E1A0D590191E06D5FCD880D9943" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:49D0EAFD-4075-45C2-9F4C-A21009AE4F38" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pyxiloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pyxiloricaria Isbrücker &amp; Nijssen 1984:163" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pyxiloricaria</taxonomicName>
more closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="C188F5527E68B037A25A499F81E66DFA" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E805457A-B6F3-4756-950E-1AD4B96002BB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudohemiodon" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudohemiodon Bleeker 1862:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudohemiodon</taxonomicName>
than other representatives of the group. Moreover, with 
<taxonomicName id="6C21BB0DE4AF09154683452D5E4F65B4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B3803885-682F-4807-A975-1839E719B4E5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Loricaria Linnaeus 1758:307" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Loricaria</taxonomicName>
, it shares filamentous lips, inconspicuous fringed 
<pageStartToken id="A43246EF4AE2D26485E34FF68C2C1162" pageNumber="35">barbels</pageStartToken>
on the lower lip, and shorter maxillary barbels. The phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName id="C78E512FD7387231034736082472BC7C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:49D0EAFD-4075-45C2-9F4C-A21009AE4F38" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pyxiloricaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pyxiloricaria Isbrücker &amp; Nijssen 1984:163" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pyxiloricaria</taxonomicName>
remains uncertain, and its presence in the 
<taxonomicName id="F4447CE00B6712684BCBDE8E0E84BDF2" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E805457A-B6F3-4756-950E-1AD4B96002BB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudohemiodon" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudohemiodon Bleeker 1862:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudohemiodon</taxonomicName>
group could be artificial, given the characters shared with 
<taxonomicName id="991D760E3E9911EA3C9C22BB28F624AD" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B3803885-682F-4807-A975-1839E719B4E5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Loricaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Loricaria Linnaeus 1758:307" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Loricaria</taxonomicName>
. Herein, following 
<normalizedToken id="5DCA10ACB64E2FBB82D66C027BD5CCAC" originalValue="Isbrücker">Isbruecker</normalizedToken>
&amp; Nijssen (1984), it is maintained in the 
<taxonomicName id="B7CA455A03361D462AAA96A3B95429A7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E805457A-B6F3-4756-950E-1AD4B96002BB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudohemiodon" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudohemiodon Bleeker 1862:3" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="34" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudohemiodon</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
